AN ACT relating to crime; authorizing a governmental entity to
disclose certain confidential information to the statewide
center for providing assistance to victims under certain
circumstances; and providing other matters properly
relating thereto.
Legislative Counsel’s Digest:
1 Existing law declares it a policy of this State to provide assistance to victims of
2 violent crimes or the dependents of victims of violent crimes. (NRS 217.010)
3 Existing law requires the Division of Child and Family Services of the Department
4 of Health and Human Services, to the extent that money is available for this
5 purpose, to designate a statewide center to provide assistance to victims. If a center
6 to provide assistance to victims is designated, existing law requires the center to
7 provide certain support services to victims, including, without limitation, referrals,
8 advocacy services and counseling. (NRS 217.096) With limited exception, this bill
9 authorizes a governmental entity to disclose certain confidential information to the
10 center for the limited purpose of providing support services to victims of crimes.
THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF NEVADA, REPRESENTED IN
SENATE AND ASSEMBLY, DO ENACT AS FOLLOWS:
1 Section 1. NRS 217.096 is hereby amended to read as follows:
2 217.096 1. In collaboration with persons and entities that
3 advocate for the needs of victims, the Division shall, to the extent
4 that money is available for this purpose, designate a statewide center
5 to provide assistance to victims.
