1 2. If a center is designated pursuant to subsection 1, the center
2 must, to the extent money is available, provide support services to
3 victims, including, without limitation, by:
4 (a) Providing referral services and case management services to
5 connect victims with:
6 (1) Necessary medical and behavioral health care services,
7 including, without limitation, counseling services and treatment for
8 post-traumatic stress;
9 (2) Agencies which provide compensation to and support for
10 victims;
11 (3) Legal aid services; and
12 (4) Services provided by a federal, state or local law
13 enforcement agency;
14 (b) Providing advocacy services for victims, including, without
15 limitation, services designed to ensure victims are reimbursed for
16 out-of-pocket expenses that are eligible for reimbursement by an
17 agency which provides compensation and support for victims;
18 (c) Providing information concerning counseling services and
19 facilitating the provision of counseling services, including, without
20 limitation, through virtual and in-person support groups and
21 wellness events;
22 (d) Providing technical assistance with applying for online
23 services available to victims;
24 (e) Operating a call center for the purpose of providing
25 information relating to support services available to victims; and
26 (f) Responding to critical incidents in this State.
27 3. If a center is designated pursuant to subsection 1, the center
28 must:
29 (a) Be based in a county whose population is 700,000 or more
30 and provide direct services to victims in that county;
31 (b) To the extent money is available, assist the Division with
32 expanding the services available to victims in this State; and
33 (c) To the extent money is available, provide training and
34 technical assistance and take other preparatory steps to ensure that
35 communities throughout the State are adequately trained and
36 equipped to provide support services to victims relating to critical
37 incidents.
38 4. Unless otherwise prohibited by federal law, a governmental
39 entity may provide confidential information to a center designated
40 pursuant to subsection 1 for the limited purpose of providing
41 support services to victims. The center shall not disclose any
42 confidential information received pursuant to this subsection, and
43 receipt of the information does not alter, affect, abrogate or waive
44 the confidential status of the information.
