1 5. The Administrator may accept any gift, grant, donation,
2 bequest or other source of money for the purposes of carrying out
3 the provisions of this section. Any money so received must be
4 deposited in the Victim Support Gift Account, which is hereby
5 established in the State General Fund. The Administrator shall
6 administer the Account. The interest and income earned on money
7 in the Account from any gift, grant, donation or bequest, after
8 deducting any applicable charges, must be credited to the Account.
9 Money from any gift, grant, donation or bequest that remains in the
10 Account at the end of the fiscal year does not revert to the State
11 General Fund, and the balance in the Account must be carried
12 forward to the next fiscal year.
13 [5.] 6. As used in this section:
14 (a) “Administrator” means the Administrator of the Division.
15 (b) “Critical incident” means an abnormal event that is sudden
16 and unexpected and has a stressful impact sufficient to overwhelm
17 the coping skills of a person.
18 (c) “Division” means the Division of Child and Family Services
19 of the Department.
20 (d) “Governmental entity” means:
21 (1) The government of this State;
22 (2) An agency of the government of this State;
23 (3) A political subdivision of this State; and
24 (4) An agency of a political subdivision of this State.
25 (e) “Victim” means a person who suffers direct harm as a result
26 of a violent crime or a person who suffers harm as an indirect
27 consequence of a violent crime, including, without limitation, by
28 witnessing the crime.
